multimediaviewer-repository-local:
Link to repository where the image is locally hosted.
See also:
* {{msg-mw|multimediaviewer-repository}}

multimediaviewer-datetime-uploaded:
Used in JavaScript code. Parameters:
* $1 - time and date (formatted)
See also:
* {{msg-mw|Multimediaviewer-datetime-created}}
{{Identical|Uploaded}}

multimediaviewer-thumbnail-error:
Text shown when the image could not be loaded. Followed by {{msg-mw|multimediaviewer-thumbnail-error-description}}.
See also:
* {{msg-mw|multimediaviewer-thumbnail-error-description}}
* {{msg-mw|multimediaviewer-metadata-error}}

multimediaviewer-permission-link:
Text of the link (on top of the metadata box) which shows additional permission (by the copyright owner via OTRS) terms

See also:
* {{msg-mw|multimediaviewer-permission-link-hide}}

multimediaviewer-permission-link-hide:
Text of the link (on top of the metadata box) which hides additional permission terms

See also:
* {{msg-mw|multimediaviewer-permission-link}}

multimediaviewer-optout-mmv:
Text for the opt-out link. Clicking on the link will turn off MediaViewer.

See also:
* {{msg-mw|Multimediaviewer-optout-pending-mmv}}
* {{msg-mw|Multimediaviewer-optin-mmv}}

multimediaviewer-optin-mmv:
Text for the opt-back link. Clicking it will undo the opt-out.

See also:
* {{msg-mw|Multimediaviewer-optin-pending-mmv}}
* {{msg-mw|Multimediaviewer-optout-mmv}}

multimediaviewer-optout-pending-mmv:
Text shown for the opt-out link while the optout request is being processed.

See also:
* {{msg-mw|Multimediaviewer-optout-mmv}}
* {{msg-mw|Multimediaviewer-optin-pending-mmv}}

multimediaviewer-optin-pending-mmv:
Text shown for the opt-in link while the optin request is being processed.

See also:
* {{msg-mw|Multimediaviewer-optin-mmv}}
* {{msg-mw|Multimediaviewer-optout-pending-mmv}}

multimediaviewer-optin-help:
Tooltip shown over the enabling link.

The link text is {{msg-mw|Multimediaviewer-optin-mmv}}.

See also:
* {{msg-mw|Multimediaviewer-optout-mmv}}
* {{msg-mw|Multimediaviewer-optout-help}}

multimediaviewer-geoloc-coord:
Format for geolocation coordinates. Parameters:
* $1 - the number of degrees
* $2 - the number of minutes
* $3 - the number of seconds (rounded to the nearest hundredths place)
* $4 - the direction symbol, defined by the following messages:
** {{msg-mw|Multimediaviewer-geoloc-north}}
** {{msg-mw|Multimediaviewer-geoloc-east}}
** {{msg-mw|Multimediaviewer-geoloc-south}}
** {{msg-mw|Multimediaviewer-geoloc-west}}

multimediaviewer-geolocation:
Message for displaying a location. Parameters:
* $1 - a location which is formatted by {{msg-mw|Multimediaviewer-geoloc-coords}}
{{Identical|Location}}

multimediaviewer-html-embed-credit-link-:
The clickable text of a link in a credit line, used when generating HTML to reuse an image.
{{Related|Multimediaviewer-embed-credit-text}}
{{Identical|Link}}

multimediaviewer-original-embed-dimensio:
Text of size selector option which will generate wikitext for a thumbnail with the original (full) size.
* $1 - thumbnail dimensions, defined by the following message:
** {{msg-mw|Multimediaviewer-embed-dimensions}}

multimediaviewer-xl-embed-dimensions:
Text of size selector option which will generate wikitext for a thumbnail with extra large size.
* $1 - thumbnail dimensions, defined by the following message:
** {{msg-mw|Multimediaviewer-embed-dimensions}}
{{Identical|Extra large}}

multimediaviewer-large-embed-dimensions:
Text of size selector option which will generate wikitext for a thumbnail with large size.
* $1 - thumbnail dimensions, defined by the following message:
** {{msg-mw|Multimediaviewer-embed-dimensions}}

{{Identical|Large}}

multimediaviewer-medium-embed-dimensions:
Text of size selector option which will generate wikitext for a thumbnail with medium size.
* $1 - thumbnail dimensions, defined by the following message:
** {{msg-mw|Multimediaviewer-embed-dimensions}}
{{Identical|Medium}}

multimediaviewer-small-embed-dimensions:
Text of size selector option which will generate wikitext for a thumbnail with small size.
* $1 - thumbnail dimensions, defined by the following message:
** {{msg-mw|Multimediaviewer-embed-dimensions}}
{{Identical|Small}}

multimediaviewer-embed-dimensions-with-f:
Collates image dimensions and a file format.
* $1 - {{msg-mw|Multimediaviewer-embed-dimensions}}
* $2 - file format extension, lowercased

multimediaviewer-attr-html:
{{optional}}
Label for a button that lets the user pick HTML as an output format.
{{Identical|HTML}}
